{
  "text": "Male testosterone deficiency is a syndrome associated with hormonal profile changes which negatively affects libido, sexual function, mood, behavior, lean body mass, and bone density [CITATION_1] . Actually, testosterone deficiency has been implicated with decline of the quality of the erections, loss of libido, osteoporosis, weight gain, muscle weakness, decreased lean body mass, diabetes mellitus and cognitive changes [CITATION_2] . The decrease in serum testosterone (T) may be due to primary testicular failure [CITATION_3] and/or dysfunction of the hypothalamic-pituitary axis [CITATION_4] . This deficiency in aging males is associated with increased Vol. 38 (4): 512-518, July -August, 2012 body weight, adipose tissue, and estrogens, due to peripheral conversion of T to estradiol [CITATION_5] . The negative feedback mechanism from excess estradiol results in a paradoxically low LH (luteinizing hormone) secretion from the pituitary despite a physiologically low T level [CITATION_6] .",
